# TopN Store

Columns:

- Key Space Size
- Portation of keys (in the keys space) each batch
  - 200% in key space 10 means there may be 20 keys (with 10 distinct values)
- Key distribution in the key space
- Value distribution (in 0~1)
- Effective rate of keys of StoreV1 (top20)
- Effective rate of values of StoreV1 (top20)
- Effective rate of keys of StoreV2 (top20)
- Effective rate of values of StoreV2 (top20)
- Effective rate of keys of StoreV3 (top20)
- Effective rate of values of StoreV3 (top20)

## Stores

- StoreV1: Evict by the sum of value (top200)
- StoreV2: Evict by the average sum of value (top200)
- StoreV3: Evict by the value of each batch (top200)
